wiki.content: “Back to Me” sees Ye and Ty Dolla $ign expand upon sexual subject material supported by Freddie Gibbs. Both Ye and Gibbs express their sexual interests while Ty Dolla $ign captures a lingering confidence, assuring his sexual partner she’ll return to him the next day. A video clip of Kanye West and Ty Dolla $ign listening to “Back To Me” surfaced via media outlet The Shade Room on October 2, 2023. An extended snippet surfaced on October 18, 2023, revealing a verse from Quavo. However, when it was debuted entirely on December 12, 2023 at the Miami Vultures Rave, Quavo’s verse was removed in favor of Freddie Gibbs. Quavo was re-added to this track by January 31, 2024, when North West and her friends donned merchandise with the Vultures tracklist, but was once again removed at the Vultures listening party.
